Additional Use Grant:

  The following uses are permitted free of charge regardless of whether
  they would otherwise constitute a Competing Use:

  (a) Research, academic study, security review, and audit of this code;
  (b) Deployment on any public testnet or private development network;
  (c) Internal evaluation and proof-of-concept where the software is
      not made available to third parties;
  (d) Integration of published interfaces (ABIs, events, return types)
      but not the core accounting or fee logic, into non-competing products;
  (e) Any use by a party that has received express written authorization
      from YearRing Fund Protocol, limited to the scope of that authorization.

  Production use outside the above is permitted only for:
  (i)  Smart contract addresses officially deployed by YearRing Fund Protocol
       and listed at:
       https://github.com/yearring-fund/YearRing-FundProtocol/blob/main/deployments/
  (ii) Parties holding a separate written license agreement with
       YearRing Fund Protocol.

Competing Use Definition:

  "Competing Use" means operating or making available to third parties,
  in a live production environment, any product or service that:

  (a) accepts deposits, subscriptions, or capital contributions from
      third parties and issues shares, units, or receipt tokens representing
      beneficial interest in a managed pool of assets;
  (b) processes redemptions or withdrawals of such instruments; and
  (c) charges management fees, performance fees, or other compensation
      for managing such pooled assets —

  where "third parties" means persons or entities other than YearRing Fund
  Protocol and its affiliates.

  The definition is intentionally business-scoped, not technical.
  Wrapping this code in a different interface does not change the analysis.

